<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - REAR PTO HOUSING ASSEMBLY REMOVAL (IF EQUIPPED) - REAR OIL SEAL CARRIER
        REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>REAR OIL SEAL CARRIER REMOVAL</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>1. THE REAR OIL SEAL IS IN THE REAR PTO HOUSING ASSEMBLY. REFER TO THE APPROPRIATE CHASSIS SERVICE
                    MANUAL FOR SERVICE PROCEDURES.
                </para>
                <para>2. THE REAR COVER CAN NOT BE REMOVED UNTIL THE FOUR (4) BOLTS MOUNTED THRU THE OIL PAN AND INTO
                    THE BOTTOM OF THE REAR COVER ARE REMOVED. REFER TO OIL PAN REMOVAL IN THIS SECTION FOR FURTHER
                    INFORMATION.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove six (6) bolts securing rear carrier to crankcase (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600738">7.38</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ). Remove carrier
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1600736" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5283" filename="../figeg5/EG5283.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.36 Removing Special Nut And Mounting Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600737" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5285" filename="../figeg5/EG5285.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.37 Removing PTO Mounting Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600738" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5277" filename="../figeg5/EG5277.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.38 Removing Rear Carrier Mounting Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
